<div id="community-vibe">
    <h2 class="sect-title">Community Vibe in Greenwood/Greenbriar </h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
        
        <p class="par-lg">Greenwood/Greenbriar is a residential area located in the Northwestern region of Calgary. At the south, it is bound by the Trans-Canada Highway and at the north, the Bow River. At the west, it’s bound by Stoney Trial and in the east, the Bowness community. The neighborhood is currently represented by the Ward 1 Councilor at the Calgary City Council.</p>
        <p class="par-xl">Parks in Greenwood/Greenbriar include the Bowmont Park, the Shouldice Pool, the Bowness Park, and the Edworthy Park etc. There are several athletic parks as well.</p>

        <p class="par-lg">The 2012 Greenwood/Greenbriar demographics indicate the town’s population to be 946 settled within 501 homes. The population density is calculated to be 790/kilometer square. The overall land area is measured to be 1.2 kilometer square.</p>


